The article provides a transcript of a press briefing held by the White House on the topic of student loan relief. The briefing featured Domestic Policy Advisor Ambassador Susan Rice and Deputy Director of the National Economic Council Bharat Ramamurti. They discussed the President's announcement to provide relief for student loan borrowers, including extending the pause on loan repayments, providing debt cancellation for Pell Grant recipients, implementing reforms to income-driven repayment plans, and making changes to the Public Service Loan Forgiveness program. They also addressed questions about the cost of the program, the impact on inflation, and the potential for colleges to raise tuition rates. The White House emphasized that the relief is targeted towards those who need it most and that the President is committed to building an economy from the bottom up and the middle out.